                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/525: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-05-20T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 20, 1929—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. Department’s 15, May 11, 6 p.m.<note n="28" xml:id="d705fn28">See footnote
                        27, <ref target="#pg_847">p. 847</ref>.</note> The Commission of Inquiry and
                    Conciliation has arranged for the repatriation of prisoners held respectively by
                    Bolivia and Paraguay. The prisoners held by Paraguay will be brought to Corumbá,
                    if the Brazilian Government consents to a request already made through the
                    Brazilian Embassy here for this purpose. When Brazilian consent is received the
                    Military Attaché at your Mission will be asked to proceed with a Brazilian
                    officer to Corumbá to assist in connection with the repatriation. Further
                    instructions will be sent for this purpose.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
